A '''crystal cluster''' is a group of [[crystal]]s which formed in an open space environment and exhibit [[euhedral]] [[Crystal habit|crystal form]] determined by their internal [[crystal structure]]. A cluster of small crystals coating the walls of a cavity are called [[Druse (geology)|druse]].

