The '''Strasskirchen Solar Park''' is a large [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Bavaria]], with an installed capacity of 54&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]]. It was developed by a joint venture of [[MEMC Electronic Materials|MEMC]] and [[Q-Cells]] in 2009. At this time this Solar Park was the second largest PV Power Plant. Q-Cells also provided the solar modules for the facility which is located in [[Straßkirchen]], [[Bavaria]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.solarplaza.com/top10-largest-pv-power-plants/|title=Top 10 World's Largest Solar PV Power Plants|accessdate=18 September 2011}}</ref><ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=13028 eXenewable Project Profile Page - Strasskirchen, PV, Germany]</ref> {{Clear}}
